	<text>
		<body>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Boston</placeName> <date>May 3th 1854</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Rev. Sir&#33;</p>
				<p>Enclosed I forward to you some resolutions&#44; which I am<lb/> ordered to get printed in your next Occident&#44; &#38; for<lb/> the expenses you will please send in your bill.<lb/>  You might be astonished for getting said resolutions<lb/> so late&#44; but I have to inform you&#44; that there is considerable<lb/> trouble since 6 months in these Congregation between the<lb/> <sic>germans</sic> &#38; Polanders for the last 11 years as you are<lb/> aware this Congregation has been carried on respectable<lb/> &#38; <sic>peacable</sic>&#44; but last <date>Sept.</date> a good <sic>menni</sic> Polanders have been<lb/> admitted&#44; &#38; troubles commenced.  Already a compromise<lb/> has been effected&#44; but when the good men of the legacy<lb/> of <persName>Judah Touro</persName> was known&#44; the leaders of the polish<lb/> party&#44; who care <sic>werri</sic> little about Judaism&#44; still want the<lb/> management of the whole&#44; could not be brought to a<lb/> <sic>peacable</sic> settlement&#44; &#38; the matter is now pending before<lb/> courts of Laws.  My <sic>objekt</sic> of mentioning to you is&#44; as<lb/> your influence to some of the executors of <persName>Judah Touro</persName><lb/> to <sic>reccomend</sic> some understanding &#38; to settle the trouble&#44;<lb/> as both parties having organized under the same Charter&#44;<lb/> &#38; each claiming the legacy &#38; the property &#38; <add>Hebrew</add><lb/> Excuse me in troubling you about such matters.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I am yours respectfully&#8212;</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><persName role="author">Moses Ehrlich</persName></p>
		</body>
